<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Novak Djokovic and his petulant tendencies flirted with disaster once too often on Sunday night when he was sensationally defaulted from the US Open.</p>

<p>The world number one was kicked out of Flushing Meadows as, in a flash of temper that has become too common, he angrily swiped a ball away that struck a female line judge in the throat.</p>

<p>Massive favourite for the tournament, the 33 year-old Serb had already been showing signs at frustration at the resistance being put up by Spain‚Äôs Pablo Carreno Busta when he was broken for 5-6 in the opening set.</p>

<p>Novak Djokovic has been disqualified from the US Open for hitting a ball at a line judge</p>

<p>Djokovic, of Serbia, checks on a lineswoman after hitting her with a ball at the US Open</p>

